				<td colspan="2"><span>My bard is now 47, I figure it's time to start gathering stuff for my epic.  I get the easy stuff done like the conversations and all. Then I notice Vox was up and figure ok awesome lets do it.  So I goto PoK and ask people there and my guild to help me out.  Sunday Night, get a good group and head at it. Well some pissy newb decides since I told her she couldn't come along to train us, she causes us to wipe badly. We try a few times but in the end to many people got fed up and left. Tried again on 
<br />

<br />
Tuesday, got a group ready and got things moving. Pull giants kill them, get ready for buffs, noone listens.. not a person listens, I say unclick buffs and crap buff 4 buffs...   and next thing I know ALL buffs are being cast every which way and all the group leaders ar elike ready! I am like no... proper bufifng didn't happen, but people started complaining and the ran the charge... first AE fear everyone goes running except my group and me and we wipe... 
<br />

<br />
Wednesday.. everything goes great, giants dead, good strong melees before the charge I told everyone unless we get chanters we need to call it off... People moaned, so we buffed and raided... vox to 30% and wipe...
<br />

<br />
Today... We get everything set, got 5 chanters, 3 clerics, a great set up, powerful and inteligent MT... Start clearing giants and get down to just the group right around Vox. I ask the Puller monk if he had ever pulled vox before He said once. So I told him to pull with the SK and tag pull the room cause Vox now warps out of room if not careful. He said I didn't know what I was talking about and pulled. We wipe when Vox warps the king room.I call evac and zone... Most of us make it out.. had like 6 deaths over all... really not a bad mess up on the pull... We wait for vox to go back to lair and start CRing and people start leaving because they didn't come to the raid to die.. and from the 24 we had all but 8 leave because the didn't expect to die during it....
<br />

<br />
This whole rant is about raiding newbs expecting everything to be flawless or thinking the raid leader doesn't need to be listened to. You really can't get a good Old World Dragon raid going cause anyone that is in the least experienced in raiding it seems are all 60+</span></td>
